//notes: In PvP Eyasluna does not reach the same ranges that Adept Fate can, while still “wasting” a perk slot on Rangefinder. However this allows it to reach into more interesting builds while not focusing wholly on range. If you prefer the feel of Eyasluna then a Rangefinder + Moving Target roll is the play for the range, but Unrelenting is a surprisingly good 6s perk, while Demo can be used to better use your now slower charging grenades. tags:pve,pvp

The combo of Overflow + Focused Fury is a 6s monster, with an overflowed pulse giving multiple more bursts with which to both proc and take advantage of he damage buff of Focused Fury. tags:pve,pvp

//notes: With the change to precision fusions in S16, Adaptives have risen in strength. Normally killing in 5 bolts at 6 resilience and below, High Impact Reserves or a charge time increase can make it 5 bolt all resilience and 9 resilience respectively. Then it’s a matter of improving the recoil direction to be as vertical as possible and getting as much stability and accuracy as you can. This is an excellent PvP fusion if you can just get a good roll on it. tags:pvp
